column1:
Person A: Hi, I'm looking for a hotel to stay in that includes free wifi. I'm looking to stay in a hotel, not a guesthouse.
Person B: Yes I have many options. What is your preferred price point?
Person A: I would like one in the moderate price range and with free parking.
Person B: I would recommend the Lovell Lodge. It is indeed a hotel despite it's name and is very cute.
Person A: Okay, please book that for 3 people and 2 nights starting from Friday.
Person B: Booking was successful. Reference number is : 9HMD04UW . anything else?
Person A: I would love to find a restaurant in the same price range as the Lovell Lodge.
Person B: In what area?
Person A: I would like the west please.
Person B: I'd recommend prezzo, its an italian restaurant on 21 - 24 Northampton Road. Would you like a table?
Person A: I'm sorry. I actually need a restaurant in the centre.
Person B: We have more than 20 moderately priced restaurants in the centre of town. Do you have a preference for cuisine?
Person A: I would like chinese. I would like that for 7pm.
Person B: We have three moderate Chinese restaurants in the centre. May I suggest the Lan Hong House?
Person A: Sounds great, thanks! Actually, can you please just tell me the postcode and address?
Person B: cb23pp postcode and the address is 11 Peas Hill City Centre
Person A: I will also need a taxi to take me between the two place. Leaving from the restaurant at 24:30
Person B: How many people for the taxi?
Person A: I don't think that matters. Can you just make sure I leave the restaurant to the hotel no later than 24:30.
Person B: Your taxi has been booked. It will be a black Toyota and the contact number is 07757106249.
Person A: Thank you so much for your help.
Person B: Enjoy your stay! Let us know if we can be of any further assistance.

Person A: Yes hello! I'm looking for a train leaving on tuesday from norwich to cambridge.
Person B: There are a total of 133 trains traveling from Norwich to Cambridge. Is there a particular day that you would like to travel on?
Person A: I will travel on Tuesday to Cambridge from Norwich, and I need to arrive by 19:15.
Person B: Perfect. Did you have a departure time in mind? You could leave norwich as early as 05:16 or as late as 17:16 and still make it on time.
Person A: Earlier in the day is safer, thanks. I just need 1 ticket on the earliest ride.
Person B: I booked TR3932, reference number is FIW5ABO2 .
Person A: Thank you, I'm also looking for place to go in town, specifically the south. What kinds of things are there to do?
Person B: There are many attractions in that area. Would you prefer a museum, nightclub, cinema, theatre or park?
Person A: I would like a museum can I have the phone number and entrance fee?
Person B: The Byard Art Museum has no entrance fee. Their phone number is 01223464646. Anything else I can help with?
Person A: That's all I need. Thanks.
Person B: You're welcome! Please contact us in the future if you need any other information. Have a great day!

Person A: I am looking for city centre north b and b
Person B: I have found the guesthouse you were wanting. Would you like me to book this for you?
Person A: Yes, please book it for 1 person and for 5 nights starting Friday.
Person B: Your booking was successful. The reference number is : BE1VD9EH .
Person A: Great, thank you so much.
Person B: You are very welcome!

Person A: Hello I want to see some authentic architectures in cambridge!
Person B: There is plenty of architectural churches in the centre. Would you like their addresses?
Person A: Please. Could you also provide their phone number and entrance fees?
Person B: Holy trinity church is in the centre of town their number is 01223355397 and they have a free entrance fee.
Person A: Okay. Wonderful. May I have the exact address as well? Also I need help finding a train to go to Stansted Airport that will arrive by 18:00.
Person B: The Holy Trinity Church's address is Market Street, postcode cb23nz. There are many trains arriving in Stansted Airport by 18:00. Would you like to narrow your search further?
Person A: Yes. I would like a direct, nonstop train.
Person B: What day and time do you want to leave?
Person A: I would like to leave from Cambridge on Friday. I need to arrive by 18:00.
Person B: There is a direct, 28 minute train from Cambridge to Stansted that leaves at 14:40 and arrives at 15:08. All other trains arrive after 16:00. Would you like me to book this?
Person A: Yes, I need 4 tickets.
Person B: Great! I have you booked for four tickets on Train TR1316 with a total fee of 40.4 GBP. Your reference number is EFGE9M7Z . Anything else?
Person A: No, thank you.
Person B: Have a great day!
Person A: Thank you. You too!
Person B: It's been my pleasure to assist you.

Person A: I want a train leaving from kings lynn.
Person B: What is your destination?
Person A: Cambridge, leaving on Wednesday after 12:00.
Person B: Train 7040 leaves kings lynn at 12:11 and arrives in cambridge at 12:58. Would you like me to book a ticket?
Person A: Yes. Book it for 3 people.
Person B: Your booking was successful and your reference number is ISO72H9I . May I help you with anything else today?
Person A: Can you recommend some places to go in the centre?
Person B: Sure, there are lots of things to choose from--colleges, architecture, museums, nightclubs, parks, boating, pools. What would interest you the most?
Person A: I'd like a museum. But I will need the entrance fee and phone number. You can pick one for me, please.
Person B: How about Castle Galleries? It's free, and their phone number is 01223307402. Can I help you with anything else?
Person A: That's it, thanks for your help.
Person B: Thank you for using our service today!

Person A: I'm looking for an expensive place to eat in the centre.
Person B: There are a lot of great, expensive restaurant in the centre. What type of food would you prefer?
Person A: It doesn't matter to me which type of food they serve. What would you recommend for a person eating alone?
Person B: How about Midsummer House Restaurant, serving British food? It's at Midsummer Common. Would you like to book a table?
Person A: Yes please, can you book a table for 1 on Monday at 13:00?
Person B: You are booked! Your table will be reserved for fifteen minutes and your reference number is RKD8KQPM .
Person A: Thanks! I also need a train to peterborough and I need it to arrive by 10am and arrive on tuesday to cambridge
Person B: I am sorry, would you like to go to or from Cambridge?
Person A: I will be departing from Cambridge and traveling to Peterborough.
Person B: Sure, I can book you on TR0162 arriving by 7:56. Will this be a reservation for 1 also?
Person A: Yes, this will be for one person only. Thank you very much
Person B: Yes your booking was successful and your reference number is P68PH2RR .
Person A: Okay thank you very much.
Person B: Okay Glad I could help you.

Person A: We would like to visit a museum while we are in town.
Person B: Okay, that sounds fun! What area are you going to be in?
Person A: We will be in the centre area. What do you suggest? Please provide phone number, postcode, and address.
Person B: I have 11 museums in the Centre. I would recommend Castle Galleries, phone number 01223307402, postal code cb23bj, address unit su43, grande arcade, saint andrews street. It is free.
Person A: Do you have any other suggestions?
Person B: You should check out Primavera. The phone number is 01223357708. It is at 10 King's Parade and the postcode is cb21sj.
Person A: I also need a train going to cambridge.
Person B: In order to find a train I need to know where you are departing from and which day.
Person A: I'm departing from birmingham new street on Saturday and I'd like to leave after 12:45.
Person B: How about TR8390 that leaves birmingham new street at 13:40 on Saturday. It arrives in cambridge at 16:23. The price is 60.08. Shall I book it?
Person A: Yes, can I book that for 5 people?
Person B: I was able to book it, reference is 0W0BQB8W .
Person A: Thank you very much
Person B: You're welcome! Can I help you with anything else?
Person A: Thank you, that's all I need today.
Person B: Please call us back if we can assist you in any other way. Have a great day! Goodbye.
